</li><li> Bosses in <em><a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Spinmaster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Spinmaster">Spinmaster</a></em>, organic ones included.
</li><li> Some bosses in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Kirby" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Kirby">Kirby</a></em> series are borderline that but a few of them (like Wham Bam bosses) are true examples. Explosions are replaced with pentagrams though.
</li><li> The first and third bosses of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Bug" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Bug">Bug</a></em> Justified for the first boss, since the giant snail's shell acts like a helicopter bomber, not so justified for the giant swamp worm.
</li><li> Except for the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/QuirkyMinibossSquad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/QuirkyMinibossSquad">Teki trio</a>, most bosses and stuff blows this way in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CannonDancer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CannonDancer">Cannon Dancer</a></em>.
</li><li> All bosses in two out of the three games which form part of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ThreeWonders" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ThreeWonders">Three Wonders</a></em>: <em>Midnight Wanderers</em> and <em>Chariot</em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MeikyuujouHydra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MeikyuujouHydra">Meikyuujou Hydra</a></em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em>Mitsume ga Tooru</em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MyLittlePonyRiseOfTheClockworkStallions" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MyLittlePonyRiseOfTheClockworkStallions">My Little Pony Rise Of The Clockwork Stallions</a></em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ChakanTheForeverMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ChakanTheForeverMan">Chakan: The Forever Man</a></em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Pulseman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Pulseman">Pulseman</a></em>.
</li><li> Bosses in <em>Ultraman Club</em>.
</li><li> Normal enemies in <em>The Great Battle IV</em>.
</li><li> The train boss, Godzilla, and the final boss in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheRevengeOfShinobi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheRevengeOfShinobi">The Revenge of Shinobi</a></em>.
</li></ul></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder6');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Real Time Strategy&nbsp;</div><div id="folder6" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> Several unit and building death animations in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarcraftII" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/StarcraftII">Starcraft II</a></em>
</li><li> The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BossInMookClothing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BossInMookClothing">Burrowing Snargets</a> in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Pikmin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Pikmin">Pikmin</a></em>
